Bring a large #pot of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry all produce. Trim and
quarter @zucchini{1}(trimmed and quartered lengthwise); cut crosswise into
½-inch-thick pieces. Mince @garlic{2%cloves}. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}.

Once water is boiling, add @spaghetti{6%ounce} to #pot. Cook until al dente,
~{9-11%minutes}. Reserve 1 cup pasta cooking water, then drain. Keep empty pot
handy for use in step 5.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp} in a large, preferably
nonstick, pan over medium-high heat. Add zucchini; cook, stirring occasionally,
until browned and softened, ~{4-6%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.
Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate. Wipe out pan.

While zucchini cooks, pat @chicken breasts{12%ounce} dry with #paper towels and
season all over with @Italian seasoning{1%tbsp}, salt, and pepper. Once zucchini
is done, heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%tsp} in same pan over
medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through,
~{5-7%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board to rest.
Once cool enough to handle, slice chicken crosswise.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in #pot used for spaghetti over medium-high heat.
Add garlic, half the lemon zest, and a pinch of @chili flakes{1%tsp}. Cook,
stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}. Stir in ½ cup reserved pasta cooking
water, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, and juice from half the lemon. Simmer
until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Turn off heat.

Add spaghetti, zucchini, @sour cream{2%tbsp}, and @butter{1%tbsp} to sauce; toss to
coat. Add half the @Parmesan cheese{1/4%cup}; season with salt and pepper.

> TIP: If needed, stir in more reserved cooking water a splash at a time until
> pasta is thoroughly coated in sauce.

Divide between #bowls and top with chicken. Top with remaining Parmesan and
lemon zest, and a pinch of chili flakes if desired. Serve with remaining lemon
wedges on the side.